Jason Epstein







 





Work experience

 Work experience



Mar 2007 - Feb 2009


Chief Information Officer + Vice President of Strategic Planning
http://www.rafaellasportswear.com




Executive team member hired by Cerberus Capital Management to restructure and position Rafaella Apparel Group as a multi-branded and multi-channel corporation. Hired into lean operation with responsibilities for managing strategic plan and improving operations and technology.      

Automated business processes, such as allocation and production planning to manage organization with reductions in head count
Negotiated contracts including EDI, telecommunications, and equipment, realizing immediate cost savings
Overhauled Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) system to improve reporting, processes, and automation 
Systemized merchandising buying and production planning processes to improve data quality
Designed and implemented new standard costing module
Engineered soft and hard allocation systems and reports 
Implemented barcode scanning programs to streamline processes and improve inventory accuracy
Executed excel-based market ordering system to automate entry of style master information and bulk orders
Implemented system controls compliant with Sarbanes-Oxley (SOX)
Set up domestic production system for new Nicole Miller sportswear license
Led interviewing and selection process for agency as part of strategic brand launch
Managed brand launch with Graj & Gustavsen branding agency ( HYPERLINK "http://www.ggny.com" www.ggny.com) including new product packaging, showroom design, online and print campaign, and company’s first website
Established partnership with Myshape.com to launch integrated ecommerce site to launch 06/2009
Responsible for “shop-in-shop” project (from concept to completion) to build Rafaella branded shops within Macy’s, Belk, and Bonton
Designed and built new network infrastructure with enterprise VMware to provide performance, reliability and recovery benefits to organization



 

Aug 2006 - Feb 2007


Chief Technology Officer + Vice President of Supply Chain Management
http://www.elietahari.com

Executive that participated in critical role facilitating 285% revenue growth during 4 years of employment.  Joined organization in 2003 after company struggled for years with technology.  Quickly turned around network operations and was promoted to Chief Technology Officer, responsible for all business applications and network operations.  Transformed technology from Elie Tahari’s major weakness to industry recognized competitive advantage. Implemented sophisticated call center that improved support response from several days to average less than one hour.  Executed change management process to control system changes that impacted complex application architecture. Further promoted to VP of Supply Chain Management in 2006.

Responsible for mapping and improving operational processes, including sales, order entry, production planning, and product development
Integral to establishing operations for European sales, order management & processing, and distribution
Established EDI communications with 3PLs in Holland and Hong Kong to manage International shipments



 

Dec 2003 - Aug 2006


Chief Technology Officer
http://www.elietahari.com




Responsible for business applications, business intelligence system, and network operations
Launched Product Lifecycle Management (PLM) software addressing product development cycle & supply chain
Customized existing ERP system to incorporate sophisticated availability controls
Selected and implemented Manhattan Associates WMS (PKMS) to improve distribution center efficiencies and manage volume growth
Executed KWI retail systems with EDI integration into ERP system
Built sophisticated web- and scanner-based market ordering system for specialty stores
Streamlined international business with drop shipment systems and country specific cost sheets
Led data warehouse, data consolidation and business intelligence project utilizing DB2 and COGNOS for which IT team was awarded IBM IT Innovation Award for Application Deployment
Created store charge back (SCA) process controls to ensure accurate chargeback accounting and visibility
Initiated project with IBM to reduce logistics costs through online bidding process resulting in a savings of $3 million dollars annually



 

Mar 2003 - Dec 2003


Vice President of Technology
http://www.elietahari.com




Stabilized and re-designed entire network infrastructure
Responsible for implementation of Cisco Voice over Internet Protocol Telephony (VoIP)
Developed IT call center with highly-responsive tiered support and monitoring to improve employee efficiency



 

Jan 1998 - Dec 2002


Founding Partner/Director of Business Development
Bind Network Solutions, LLC

Founded technology consulting company in 1998 and successfully sold business in 2002.  Responsibilities included technical project sales, management of engineering team (9 full-time employees and various subcontractors), development of strategic initiatives, supervision of short and long-term financial planning & controls, and technical project management. In 2002, Bind was ranked #14 in list recognizing Top 100 Fastest Growing Private Companies in San Francisco Bay Area by San Francisco Business Times. 
Founding Partner


Developed Bind’s strategic technology initiatives and oversaw their successful execution
Led company in 196% growth from January 1999 through December 2001
Developed models used to analyze financial health of company; these models were used to track utilization rates, costs, and performance
Financed company personally and grew business with positive cash flow

Director of Business Development


Managed implementations of  Windows 2000, Exchange 2000, network infrastructure and network security
Developed high-level network architecture and infrastructure design plans for clients including Marakon Associates, Walmart.com, Fax & File Legal Services & Guru.com, Inc.
Developed criteria for bi-annual performance review and employee compensation/bonus plans
Managed resource and financial concerns for major implementations such as IT overhaul and rollout for San Francisco University High School



 

Jul 1995 - Dec 1997


System Engineer
NCR Corp. (Formerly AT&T GIS)

Gained broad enterprise technology experience as systems engineer, followed by lateral move to NCR Microsoft Professional Services Group (PSG) during divesture in 1996. 

Deployed enterprise-based computer systems with particular focus on Windows NT platform and Microsoft Exchange Server 5.5, NCR Life-Keeper for NT, and Microsoft Cluster Services
Completed nationwide rollout of  TCP/IP-based time reporting system to AT&T Solutions which entailed coordinating implementation for over 50 sites








