Summary






Executive with expertise in operational efficiencies and reduction of SG&A, strategic planning, technology and management
Proven leadership skills, with ability to effectively motivate teams and individuals on company objectives
Thorough understanding of operational aspects, coupled with strong analytical and quantitative skills
Extensive technical knowledge of high-level technology infrastructure design
Detailed understanding of apparel product development lifecycle and supply chain from concept to consumer






Awards and Recognitions




Apparel Magazine 2004 All Star Award
IBM 2006 Innovation Award for Application Deployment
Presenter at 2006 WWD Technology Forum, Presented “Implementing PLM and Beyond”
Speaker at American Apparel and Footwear Association’s Conference “Transforming Innovative Strategies into Operational Excellence” in September 2006
Ranked #14in list recognizing Top 100 Fastest Growing Private Companies in San Francisco Bay Area by San Francisco Business Times






Objective



Jason Epstein is a person who leads change in organizations to facilitate innovation and improve operations.  
Seeking an executive operations and technology role within an organization with a supply chain and/or retail. Looking to leverage existing experience as well as an opportunity to grow and learn.  Interesting in a company that seeing an opportunity to transform their business and position for explosive growth.  Excel in an entrepreneurial culture







